content.content: 1. For the purpose of clause 30 (f) of the Act, “pending before the Ontario Court (General Division)” means before the Ontario Court (General Division) on an appeal from the Commissioner; “proceedings” does not include a court action started in the District Court before September 1, 1990 when it was merged with the Ontario Court (General Division). content.raw_html:
1. For the purpose of clause 30 (f) of the Act,

“pending before the Ontario Court (General Division)” means before the Ontario Court (General Division) on an appeal from the Commissioner;

“proceedings” does not include a court action started in the District Court before September 1, 1990 when it was merged with the Ontario Court (General Division). O. Reg. 466/94, s. 1.
